        {
          "username": "Denise Brown",
          "rating": 3,
          "contributor_id": "112202690715101757462",
          "user_review_count": 16,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIAAr4UDBHZCZwmEEOFBjt9ErQzm6r5X737gd0bNQRpKAakXw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "There\u2019s a saying\u2014you don\u2019t truly appreciate something until you realize how much it matters.\n\nDuring my stay at Harlem Hospital Center, I came to appreciate something many people overlook: the quiet work that keeps patients safe and comfortable every day.\n\nCarlos Rojas from the Environmental Services (EVS) department does exactly that. He comes in, does his job with care and precision, and leaves behind a space that feels clean, fresh, and safe. It may seem simple, but it makes a real difference\u2014especially when you are trying to rest and recover.\n\nWhat stood out to me most is the consistency. Every time Carlos cleaned my room, I could feel the difference. There was a sense of calm and comfort in the environment that helped me feel at ease.\n\nSome roles are essential but often go unnoticed. Carlos is one of those people who shows up, does the job right, and makes a meaningful impact without needing recognition\u2014but he absolutely deserves it.\n\nThank you, Carlos, for your professionalism and care. Your work truly matters.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT204MVducEhMVk5wTUVZdE1sRjRibHByUjNOclRVRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x66994989947e146f!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOm81WnpHLVNpMEYtMlF4blprR3NrTUE%7C%7C?hl=en",
