          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjwC9SmFIBGENHk9i1VQafovXFEzTAwf3a5v3YBdyRamZaseJcJw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "My baby had to go to the Harlem hospital recently for head trauma. He had a gash in the middle of the forehead that needed stitches. They assessed him, kept me informed, staff was friendly. One of the ER nurses was masterful at gaining rapport and making us parents feel comfortable. They didn't have a plastic surgeon working but provided an oral maxillofacial resident instead. There were also ants crawling in the room and the windows and walls had like white spray or something running down. Overall, the experience with the staff was good. Could stand to be a bit cleaner.",
